=== Sprint 1 · Task S1.2: Wire OMS 15-state state machine ===
Date: 2026-05-27
Plan: docs/plan/2026-05-27-整改与执行计划.md §3.S1.2

--- Problem ---
Orders were submitted directly to the broker with no state tracking in PG. The `oms` package had a full 15-state machine implementation (statemachine.go, repo.go, broker.go, adapter_mt.go) with transition validation and PG persistence, but it was never wired into the order placement path. TradeEvents published to NATS had hardcoded FromState/ToState ("NEW"/"SUBMITTED") with no relationship to actual state transitions.

--- Fix ---
Part 1 — mthub/oms_writer.go (NEW):
- Self-contained OMS state writer with local state constants (avoids circular dependency: oms/adapter_mt.go imports mthub for OrderExecutor)
- 12 state constants: NEW, VALIDATED, RISK_APPROVED, SUBMITTED, WORKING, PARTIALLY_FILLED, FILLED, CANCELLED, REJECTED, FAILED, EXPIRED
- `isValidOMSTransition()` — full transition table mirroring oms.isValid() (7 state groups, all valid transitions)
- `InsertOrder()` — INSERT INTO orders with state=NEW, ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING for idempotency
- `Transition()` — validates transition, UPDATEs orders state in PG, publishes NATS event
- `IdempotencyKey()` — deterministic order ID: "ord-{accountID}-{clientID}"

Part 2 — mthub/service.go — PlaceOrder modifications:
- Added `omsWriter *OmsWriter` field + `SetOmsWriter()` setter
- After idempotency check: InsertOrder with state=NEW
- After pipeline passes: Transition(NEW → VALIDATED), Transition(VALIDATED → RISK_APPROVED)
- Pipeline rejects: Transition(NEW → REJECTED)
- No pipeline configured: auto-approve to RISK_APPROVED
- Broker session not found: Transition(RISK_APPROVED → FAILED)
- Broker PlaceOrder error: Transition(RISK_APPROVED → FAILED)
- Broker success: Transition(RISK_APPROVED → SUBMITTED)
- TradeEvent FromState changed from hardcoded "NEW" to string(OMSStateRiskApproved)

Part 3 — cmd/server/main.go:
- `omsWriter := mthub.NewOmsWriter(pool, eventStore)`
- `mthubSvc.SetOmsWriter(omsWriter)`

Circular dependency resolution:
- oms/adapter_mt.go imports mthub (for OrderExecutor interface)
- mthub cannot import oms without creating a cycle
- Solution: duplicated state constants and transition table in mthub/oms_writer.go
- Tradeoff: transition rules live in two places (oms/statemachine.go + mthub/oms_writer.go)
- Future: extract shared types to oms/types.go or internal/omstypes/

